# No Cursor Co-Author Trailer

Never include `Co-authored-by: Cursor` in git commit messages — not when writing commits, amending, squashing, or preparing PRs.

Forbidden (never add):

```
Co-authored-by: Cursor <cursoragent@cursor.com>
```

Also avoid any variant (`Co-authored-by: cursor`, `@cursor.com`, etc.).

When committing:

- Write commit messages with only the human author's attribution (e.g. `Signed-off-by` when the project requires DCO).
- After `git commit` or `git commit --amend`, check the message; if a hook or tool injected `Co-authored-by: Cursor`, remove it and amend again (or use `git commit-tree` if amend keeps re-adding it).
- When squashing commits, strip this trailer from the final message.
